==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rodent
<hw>Ro"dent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>rodens</ets>,
<ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>rodere</ets> to gnaw. See
<er>Rase</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>, and cf. <er>Rostrum</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Gnawing; biting; corroding; <fld>(Med.)</fld> applied
to a destructive variety of cancer or ulcer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Gnawing.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>Of or pertaining to the Rodentia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rodent</ent>⟦br⟧

